Can we talk about the meaning of a “boss babe”, especially how it relates to being a mom too? For me it means 60-80 hour work weeks while also trying to juggle school pick up and drops offs, sports schedules, cupcakes for school activities, quality time with my girls, lunches and snacks and permission slips and our families entire lives. I built my business while also raising my babies. This doesn’t mean men don’t work hard, but us women are held to such a double standard. We’re supposed to do it all. We’re supposed to want to stay home and raise our babies but also grow a career. Juggling boss babe and super mom becomes so heavy sometimes and we’re just expected to do it all. Just a reminder that it’s ok to want the career and also to be a great mom 💗 I’m proud that I’m showing my girls they can do and be anything while building a company and also being the mom they can always count on. #momlife #momstruggles #yougotthismomma #girlmom #boutiqueowner #cheermom #bossbabe #workingmom #siouxfalls #busineesowner hair @han_murray_ makeup @meganbertschbeauty

⭐️REAL TALK…Do you ever watch tik toks or reels and wonder if you’re doing it all wrong? As parents I think we all have those thoughts sometimes but here’s why we don’t do gentle parenting in our crazy household. 🫣😂 

1. **Negotiations? I’m Not a Lawyer!** 🤷‍♀️
 Trying to negotiate anything with a tween is like trying to convince a cat to take a bath. It doesn’t end well. We set expectations and they can choose to follow them or not. If they don’t, there’s consequences. 🤷🏼‍♀️

2. **Inside Voices? What Are Those?** 📣
 With three girls, our volume knob is permanently stuck on ‘loud’. I’ve heard that in gentle parenting, you’re supposed to speak softly and calmly. Well, in my world, if you’re not screaming like a crazy person, no one knows you even exist 😂

3. **The Art of Selective Hearing** 👂
 I’ve mastered the art of selective hearing. Trust me, it’s a survival skill when 15 little girls sleeping over are screaming the TGLC 2022 cheer routine. “Time of revival 3:05”.

4. **Structured Chaos is My Jam!** 🎉
 In the gentle parenting world, calm and order reign supreme. In my house? We prefer structured chaos. It’s like a party where the guests are a bit wild, the host is slightly tipsy, but everyone’s having a blast. WINE is also a basic necessity!

5. Please” and “Thank You”? More Like “Now” and “Seriously”!** 🤨
 While I appreciate the magic of ‘please’ and ‘thank you’, with three girls, sometimes my requests sound more like, “Put your shoes on, now!” and “Seriously, where did all this crap come from?”

6. The Art of Bribery 🍪
 I’ve read that in gentle parenting, bribery is frowned upon. But in my world, it’s an art form. “You wanna have friends over…great, I need to see your bedroom floor first!” It’s all about motivating and BRIBERY 🫣🤷🏼‍♀️

Who else is in the “I love you, but your life will not end well if you don’t listen” club? 😂💕 

Noted to say: I believe different parenting works for different families. This is just what works for ours 💕

#MomLife #ParentingUnfiltered #LoudHouseLove
